    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-01T01:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-01T01:35:00-05:00" n="335"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A14/741: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hornibrook</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-01T10:00:00+03:25"
                            >March 1, 1935—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 1—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Foreign Office urgently requests that in the event of elimination of
                    reservation to Arms Traffic Convention<note n="2" xml:id="d335fn2">For text of
                        the convention, see <ref target="frus1925v01#pg_61">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, 1925, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                            61</ref>; for text of the reservation, introduced by Senator King of
                        Utah and adopted by the Senate June 15, 1934, see <ref
                            target="frus1934v01#pg_462">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, 1934, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                            462</ref>.</note> that some official statement be made at the same time
                    so action will not be construed by other powers as Senate repudiation of any
                    rights Persia may have in the Gulf.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hornibrook</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
